Historical Background Mithila, historically known as Videha, was one of the prominent kingdoms in ancient India. It gained significant importance during the late Vedic period. The kingdom was ruled by a line of kings known as the Janakas. The most celebrated among them was King Janaka, the father of Sita, who is a central figure in the Indian epic, the Ramayana. Sita's association with Mithila has bestowed the region with immense religious and cultural significance.
