Mithila was a center of learning and philosophy. Scholars from this region contributed to various fields, including philosophy, literature, and art. The region's commitment to education and culture has been a defining characteristic throughout its history.

ğŸ—ºï¸ Geography and Demographics
Geographically, Mithila spans across the northern part of Bihar and extends into the eastern Terai region of Nepal. The major cities in the Indian part of Mithila include Darbhanga, Madhubani, Samastipur, Saharsa, and Sitamarhi. In Nepal, Janakpur holds significant cultural and historical importance.

The region is predominantly inhabited by the Maithil people, who speak the Maithili language. Maithili is an Indo-Aryan language with a rich literary tradition. It is one of the 22 scheduled languages of India and is also recognized in the constitution of Nepal.

