ğŸ¨ Madhubani Paintings
One of the most celebrated art forms originating from Mithila is the Madhubani painting, also known as Mithila painting. Traditionally practiced by women, these paintings are characterized by intricate patterns and vibrant colors. They often depict mythological themes, nature, and social events. The art form has gained international recognition and is a symbol of the region's rich cultural heritage.
