ğŸ§µ Attire and Ornaments
Traditional Maithil attire is both elegant and symbolic. Men often wear Dhoti-Kurta along with the Paag, a traditional turban symbolizing honor. Women adorn themselves in Sarees, often with intricate borders and designs. Jewelry plays a significant role, with ornaments like Tikuli (forehead decoration) and Hansuli (neckpiece) being popular.

ğŸ“š Literature and Language
The Maithili language boasts a rich literary tradition. Ancient texts, poems, and plays have been composed in Maithili, reflecting the region's intellectual heritage. Prominent literary figures like Vidyapati, a 14th-century poet, have contributed immensely to Maithili literature. His compositions, especially love songs dedicated to Lord Shiva and Goddess Parvati, are celebrated to this day.

