ğŸ›ï¸ Religious Significance
Mithila holds immense religious importance. It's considered the birthplace of Goddess Sita, making it a pivotal region in the Ramayana. Temples like the Janaki Mandir in Janakpur attract devotees from across the globe. The region also has associations with other religious figures and traditions, including Jainism and Buddhism.
